response:
Let $x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_n$ be such numbers. By AM-GM, we have 
\begin{align*}
\frac{x_1 + x_2 + \cdots + x_n}{n} \geq \sqrt[n]{x_1x_2\cdots x_n}. 
\end{align*}
Thus
\begin{align*}
\frac{1000}{n} &\geq \sqrt[n]{x_1x_2\cdots x_n}, \\
(1000/n)^n &\geq x_1x_2\cdots x_n. 
\end{align*}
AH aa. Our hand can compute multi-variable exponentials, no symboltable here. 
\begin{align*}
\frac{x_1^4 + x_2^4 + \cdots + x_n^4}{n} &\geq \sqrt[n]{x_1^4x_2^4\cdots x_n^4}\\
512000/n &\geq (x_1x_2\cdots x_n)^4 \\
n(512000/n)^4 &\geq (x_1x_2\cdots x_n)^4, \\
\sqrt[4]{n(512000/n)^4} &\geq (x_1x_2\cdots x_n).
\end{align*}
Finally, follow AM-GM again,
\begin{align*}
\frac{1000}{n} &\geq \sqrt[4]{n(512000/n)^4}\\
\text{ or }1000n^{3/4} &\geq (512000)^{1/4}n \\
8000 &\geq n.
\end{align*}
<answer> $8000.$
</answer>

